original: Jonsson, Hans Jakob Sigfrid, komminister, Tutaryd, f. 29/8/09 i Alguts-boda, Kronob. 1., av glasbruksmäst. Carl Alfred J. o. Emma Jacobsson. G. 47 m. Gertrud Ohlsson. — Stud:ex. i Växjö 30, teol. fil. ex. i Lund 32, teol. kand. 37, prakt. teol. prov 38, prästv. f. Växjö stift 39. Tjg. s. past:adj. i Högsby, Runsten o. Ber-ga, past:adj. o. v. pastor i Ekeberga, v. kommin. i Nye, past:adj. i Visse-fjärda, Lenhovda o. Linneryd, v. kommin. i Färgaryd o. Söderåkra, kommin. i Tutaryd sed. 44.
translated: Jonsson, Hans Jakob Sigfrid, vicar, Tutaryd, b. August 29th, 1909 in Algutsboda, Kronoberg. Son of glassworks manager Carl Alfred J. and Emma Jacobsson. Married in 1947 to Gertrud Ohlsson. - High school degree from Växjö in 1930, theology degree from Lund University in 1932, theology candidate in 1937, practical theology exam in 1938, ordained priest from the Växjö diocese in 1939. Served as temporary assistant pastor in Högsby, Runsten and Berga, assistant pastor and interim pastor in Ekeberga, assistant vicar in Nye, assistant pastor in Vissfjärda, Lenhovda and Linneryd, assistant vicar in Färgaryd and Söderåkra, and vicar in Tutaryd since 1944.

education.educationalCredentialAwarded: Ordained priest from the Växjö diocese
